dState-01.Definition: Indicates which elements are required by the state.

dCustomConfiguration-01.Definition: This is the title of the custom data element created to collect information that is not defined formally in NEMSIS Version 3.
dCustomConfiguration-01.V3Changes: Added to allow customized data elements to be inserted and collected from within the NEMSIS Version 3 standard.

dCustomConfiguration-02.Definition: The definition of the custom element and how it should be used.

dCustomConfiguration-03.Definition: The data type of the custom element.

dCustomConfiguration-04.Definition: Indication if the data element will accept multiple values.
dCustomConfiguration-04.V3Changes: Added to allow customized data elements to be inserted and collected from within the NEMSIS Version 3 standard.

dCustomConfiguration-05.Definition: The Usage (Mandatory, Required, Recommended, or Optional) for the Custom Data Element.
dCustomConfiguration-05.V3Changes: Added to allow customized data elements to be inserted and collected from within the NEMSIS Version 3 standard.

dCustomConfiguration-06.Definition: The values which are associated with the Custom Data Element. Values would be the choices provided to the user when they document the Custom Data Element
dCustomConfiguration-06.V3Changes: Added to allow customized data elements to be inserted and collected from within the NEMSIS Version 3 standard.

dCustomConfiguration-07.ElementName: Custom Data Element Potential NOT Values (NV)
dCustomConfiguration-07.Definition: NOT Values (NV) associated with the custom element

dCustomConfiguration-08.ElementName: Custom Data Element Potential Pertinent Negative Values (PN)
dCustomConfiguration-08.Definition: Pertinent Negative Values (PN) associated with the custom element

dAgency-01.Definition: The unique ID assigned to the EMS Agency which is associated with all state licensure numbers and information.

dAgency-02.Definition: The state-assigned provider number of the responding agency

dAgency-03.Definition: The formal name of the agency.

dAgency-04.Definition: The state/territory which assigned the EMS agency number.

dAgency-05.Definition: The states in which the EMS Agency provides services including the state associated with the EMS Agency Number.

dAgency-06.Definition: The county(ies) within each state for which the agency formally provides service.

dAgency-07.Definition: The US census tracts in which the EMS agency formally provides service.

dAgency-08.ElementName: EMS Agency Service Area ZIP Codes
dAgency-08.Definition: The ZIP codes for the EMS Agencys service area.

dAgency-09.Definition: The primary service type provided by the agency.

Codes.9920013: Medical Transport (Convalescent, Interfacility Transfer Hospital and Nursing Home)

dAgency-10.Definition: The other service type(s) which are provided by the agency.

Codes.9920013: Medical Transport (Convalescent, Interfacility Transfer Hospital and Nursing Home)

dAgency-11.Definition: The level of service which the agency provides EMS care for every request for service (the minimum certification level). This may be the license level granted by the state EMS office.

dAgency-12.Definition: The primary organizational status of the agency. The definition of Volunteer or Non-Volunteer is based on state or local definitions.

dAgency-13.Definition: The organizational structure from which EMS services are delivered (fire, hospital, county, etc.)

dAgency-14.Definition: The EMS Agencies business/corporate organizational tax status

dAgency-15.Definition: The calendar year to which the information pertains for the EMS Agency and the specific EMS Agency Number (dAgency.02).

dAgency-16.Definition: The total square miles in the agencys service area.

dAgency-17.Definition: The total population in the agencys service area based if possible on year 2010 census data.

dAgency-18.ElementName: 911 EMS Call Center Volume per Year
dAgency-18.Definition: The number of 911 calls received by the call center during the last calendar year

dAgency-19.Definition: The number of EMS dispatches during the last calendar year

dAgency-20.ElementName: EMS Patient Transport Volume per Year
dAgency-20.Definition: The number of EMS transports per year based on last calendar year.

dAgency-21.ElementName: EMS Patient Contact Volume per Year
dAgency-21.Definition: The number of EMS patient contacts per year based on last calendar year.

dAgency-22.Definition: The number of EMS patient encounters which are billable based on the last calendar year.

dAgency-23.Definition: The time zone for the EMS Agency.

dAgency-24.ElementName: EMS Agency Daylight Savings Time Use
dAgency-24.Definition: Indicate if the EMS Agency conforms to Daylight Savings Time.

dAgency-25.Definition: The National Provider Identifier issued by CMS.

dAgency-26.Definition: The state assigned Fire Department ID Number for EMS Agency(ies) operating within a Fire Department.
dAgency-26.V3Changes: Added to better associate Fire and EMS licensure and operational identifiers.

dContact-01.Definition: The contact type within the EMS agency.

dContact-02.Definition: The Last Name of the agencys primary contact.

dContact-03.Definition: The first name of the agencys primary contact.

dContact-04.Definition: The middle name or initial of the agencys primary contact.

dContact-05.Definition: The street address of the agency contacts mailing address.

dContact-06.Definition: The city of the EMS contacts mailing address.

dContact-07.Definition: The state of the Agency contacts mailing address.

dContact-08.Definition: The ZIP code of the Agencys contacts mailing address.

dContact-09.Definition: The Country code of the Agencys contacts mailing address.

dContact-11.Definition: The primary email address of the Agency contact.

dContact-12.Definition: The primary website address of the agency.

dContact-13.Definition: The medical school degree type of the EMS Medical Director.

dContact-14.ElementName: Agency Medical Director Board Certification Type
dContact-14.Definition: Documentation of the type of board certification of the EMS Agency Medical Director.

dContact-16.ElementName: EMS Medical Director Fellowship Trained Status
dContact-16.Definition: Indication if the EMS Medical Director is Fellowship trained.

dConfiguration-01.ElementName: State Associated with the Certification/Licensure Levels
dConfiguration-01.Definition: The state associated with the state certification/licensure levels.

dConfiguration-02.Definition: All of the potential levels of certification/licensure for EMS personnel recognized by the state.

dConfiguration-03.Definition: A list of all of the procedures permitted by the EMS Agencys licensing state.

dConfiguration-04.Definition: A list of all of the medications permitted by the state to be used by each EMS state certification/licensure level.
dConfiguration-04.V3Changes:
State EMS systems which have regulatory authority to identify medications to be administered within the state may identify specific RxNorm codes based on medical direction and their own need.

List of medications based on RxNorm (RXCUI) code.

Reference the NEMSIS Suggested Lists at: http://nemsis.org/v3/resources.html

RxNorm
Website - http://uts.nlm.nih.gov

Product - UMLS Metathesaurus
Website - http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm/docs/rxnormfiles.html
Product - RxNorm Full Monthly Release

dConfiguration-05.Definition: A list of all of the protocols permitted by the state.
dConfiguration-05.V3Changes: Added to better identify states with statewide protocols and define state EMS capability and care.

Codes.9914017: Cardiac Arrest-Ventricular Fibrillation/ Pulseless Ventricular Tachycardia
Codes.9914075: General-Universal Patient Care/ Initial Patient Contact
Codes.9914183: General-Law Enforcement - Blood for Legal Purposes
Codes.9914185: General-Law Enforcement - Assist with Law Enforcement Activity
Codes.9914201: Cardiac Arrest-Determination of Death / Withholding Resuscitative Efforts

dConfiguration-06.ElementName: EMS Certification Levels Permitted to Perform Each Procedure
dConfiguration-06.Definition: EMS certification levels which are permitted to perform the procedure listed in dConfiguration.07.

dConfiguration-07.Definition: A list of all procedures that the agency has implemented and available for use by any/all EMS certification levels.

dConfiguration-08.ElementName: EMS Certification Levels Permitted to Administer Each Medication
dConfiguration-08.Definition: All EMS certification levels which are permitted to administer the medications listed in dConfiguration.09 (EMS Agency Medications).

dConfiguration-09.Definition: A list of all medications the agency has implemented and have available for use.

dConfiguration-10.Definition: A list of all of the EMS field protocols that the agency has in place and available for use.

Codes.9914017: Cardiac Arrest-Ventricular Fibrillation/ Pulseless Ventricular Tachycardia
Codes.9914075: General-Universal Patient Care/ Initial Patient Contact
Codes.9914183: General-Law Enforcement - Blood for Legal Purposes
Codes.9914185: General-Law Enforcement - Assist with Law Enforcement Activity
Codes.9914201: Cardiac Arrest-Determination of Death / Withholding Resuscitative Efforts

dConfiguration-11.Definition: Special training or services provided by the EMS Agency and available to the EMS service area/community.

Codes.1211033: Water or Ice Related Rescue (Incl Swift Water)

dConfiguration-12.Definition: Indication of whether the EMS agency routinely bills for any segment of the patient population.

dConfiguration-13.ElementName: Emergency Medical Dispatch (EMD) Provided to EMS Agency Service Area
dConfiguration-13.Definition: Indication as to whether Emergency Medical Dispatch is provided to the EMS Agencys service area.

Codes.1213003: Yes, 100% of the EMS Agencys Service Area
Codes.1213005: Yes, Less than 100% of the EMS Agencys Service Area

dConfiguration-14.Definition: The vendor or company associated with the EMD Card set and algorithms.

dConfiguration-15.Definition: The EMS Agencys patient monitoring capability which can be provided to any/all patients presenting to EMS.

dConfiguration-16.Definition: The EMS crew call sign used to dispatch and communicate with the unit.  This may be the same as the EMS Unit/Vehicle Number in many agencies.

dConfiguration-17.Definition: The name or ID of the dispatch center (Primary or Secondary Service Answering Point - PSAP) that dispatches the EMS agency.
dConfiguration-17.V3Changes: Added to the dataset to assist in identifying the CAD / dispatch center providing information to the EMS agency and ePCR when there are multiple dispatch centers sending resources to the same EMS incident.

dLocation-01.Definition: The type of EMS Location which could be a fixed station or a pre-determined staging area.
dLocation-01.V3Changes: Added to allow multiple locations to be documented for an EMS Agency.

dLocation-02.Definition: The name of the EMS Location.

dLocation-03.Definition: The ID number of the EMS Location.

dLocation-04.Definition: The GPS coordinate of  the EMS location.

dLocation-05.ElementName: EMS Location US National Grid Coordinates
dLocation-05.Definition: The US National Grid Coordinates of the EMS location.

dLocation-06.Definition: The address of the EMS Location.

dLocation-07.Definition: The city of the EMS location type (e.g., Fixed station, sub-station, staging area, etc.).

dLocation-08.Definition: The state of the EMS Location.

dLocation-09.ElementName: EMS Station or Location ZIP Code
dLocation-09.Definition: The ZIP code of the EMS Location.

dLocation-10.Definition: The county of the EMS Location

dLocation-11.Definition: The country of the EMS location.

dLocation-12.Definition: The phone number of the EMS Location.

dVehicle-01.Definition: The unique ID number for the unit which is specific for each vehicle. This ID number may be the states vehicles permit number.

dVehicle-02.Definition: The manufacturers VIN associated with the vehicle.

dVehicle-03.Definition: The EMS unit number used to dispatch and communicate with the unit. This may be the same as the EMS Unit/Vehicle Number in many agencies.

dVehicle-04.Definition: The vehicle type of the unit (ambulance, fire, truck, etc.).

Codes.1404017: Quick Response Vehicle (Non-Transport Vehicle other than Fire Apparatus)

dVehicle-05.Definition: The certification/licensure level of the ambulance by the state or the certification/licensure level at which the vehicle is most commonly staffed.

dVehicle-06.ElementName: Number of Each EMS Personnel Level on Normal 911 Ambulance Response
dVehicle-06.Definition: The number of each personnel level associated with the vehicle crew.

dVehicle-07.ElementName: Number of Each EMS Personnel Level on Normal 911 Response (Non-Transport) Vehicle
dVehicle-07.Definition: The number of each personnel level for your EMS Agencys Medical (Non-911) Non-Transport Ambulance.

dVehicle-08.ElementName: Number of Each EMS Personnel Level on Normal Medical (Non-911) Transport Ambulance
dVehicle-08.Definition: The number of each personnel level for your EMS Agencys Medical (Non-911) Transport Ambulance.

dVehicle-09.Definition: Initial costs of vehicles held by agency excluding all medical and other equipment not associated with the vehicle. This cost should be inclusive of all sources of funding including grants, donations, and any other capital.

dVehicle-10.Definition: The year the vehicle was manufactured.

dVehicle-11.Definition: The year the hours and miles/kilometers were accumulated.

dVehicle-12.Definition: The number of hours the vehicle was in service for the agency for the defined year.

dVehicle-13.Definition: The number of miles/kilometers the vehicle accumulated in service for the agency for the defined year (Odometer Reading).

dPersonnel-01.Definition: The last name of the personnel.

dPersonnel-02.Definition: The first name of the personnel.

dPersonnel-03.Definition: The middle name or initial of the personnel.

dPersonnel-04.Definition: The Street or PO Box of the personnels mailing address.

dPersonnel-05.Definition: The city of the personnels mailing address.

dPersonnel-06.Definition: The state of the personnels mailing address.

dPersonnel-07.Definition: The ZIP code of the personnels mailing address.

dPersonnel-08.Definition: The country of the personnel mailing address.

dPersonnel-09.Definition: The phone number for the personnel.

dPersonnel-10.Definition: The primary email address of the personnel.

dPersonnel-13.Definition: The personnels race as defined by the OMB (US Office of Management and Budget).

Codes.1513009: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander

dPersonnel-14.Definition: The documentation of the personnels citizenship.

dPersonnel-15.Definition: The highest educational degree completed by the personnel.

Codes.1515017: High School Graduate-Diploma or the Equivalent (GED)
Codes.1515019: Some College Credit, but Less than 1 Year
Codes.1515021: 1 or More Years of College, No Degree
Codes.1515029: Professional Degree (i.e. MD, DDS, DVM, LLB, JD)

dPersonnel-16.ElementName: EMS Personnels Degree Subject/Field of Study
dPersonnel-16.Definition: The area of the personnels post high-school (post-secondary) degree.

Codes.1516005: Area, Ethnic, Cultural, and Gender Studies
Codes.1516033: Health Professions and Related Clinical Sciences, Not Including Emergency Medical Services
Codes.1516037: Liberal Arts and Sciences, General Studies, and Humanities
Codes.1516047: Not Classified by Field of Study
Codes.1516051: Parks, Recreation, Leisure and Fitness Studies
Codes.1516063: Security and Protective Services, Not Including Fire Science

dPersonnel-17.ElementName: EMS Personnels Motor Vehicle License Type
dPersonnel-17.Definition: The type of motor vehicle license (i.e. Class A, B, Pilot, etc.) of the EMS personnel.

dPersonnel-19.Definition: The year associated with each immunization type.

dPersonnel-20.Definition: The languages spoken (other than English) by the personnel with at least an elementary level of proficiency.
dPersonnel-20.V3Changes: Added to better describe the EMS workforce.

dPersonnel-21.Definition: The local agency ID number for the personnel.

dPersonnel-22.Definition: The state of the certification/licensure ID number assigned to the personnel member.

dPersonnel-23.ElementName: EMS Personnels States Licensure ID Number
dPersonnel-23.Definition: The states licensure/certification ID number for the personnel.

dPersonnel-24.ElementName: EMS Personnels State EMS Certification Licensure Level
dPersonnel-24.Definition: The personnels state EMS certification level.

dPersonnel-25.ElementName: EMS Personnels State EMS Current Certification Date
dPersonnel-25.Definition: The date of the personnels current EMS certification/licensure.

dPersonnel-26.ElementName: EMS Personnels Initial States Licensure Issue Date
dPersonnel-26.Definition: The date on which the EMS personnels states EMS certification/licensure was originally issued. This is the date of the first certification/licensure for the EMS level.

dPersonnel-27.ElementName: EMS Personnels Current States Licensure Expiration Date
dPersonnel-27.Definition: The date on which the EMS personnels (highest) state EMS certification/licensure expires.

dPersonnel-28.Definition: The National Registry number associated with the level of certification/licensure obtained through NREMT.

dPersonnel-29.ElementName: EMS Personnels National Registry Certification Level
dPersonnel-29.Definition: The level of the current National Registry of Emergency Medical Technicians (NREMT) certification.

dPersonnel-30.ElementName: EMS Personnels Current National Registry Expiration Date
dPersonnel-30.Definition: The date on which the EMS Personnels National Registry of EMTs certification/licensure expires

dPersonnel-31.Definition: The personnels primary employment status for this agency.

Codes.1531007: Neither an Employee Nor a Volunteer

dPersonnel-33.Definition: The date the employee was hired by the EMS agency for this current job.

dPersonnel-34.ElementName: EMS Personnels Primary EMS Job Role
dPersonnel-34.Definition: The individuals primary/main EMS role at the EMS agency. This is the function which is performed the majority of the time for the EMS personnel.

dPersonnel-35.Definition: The EMS personnels other job responsibilities at the agency beyond their primary role documented in dPersonnel.34 (EMS Personnels Primary EMS Job Role).

dPersonnel-36.ElementName: EMS Personnels Total Length of Service in Years
dPersonnel-36.Definition: The personnels total length of EMS service at any level (years).

dPersonnel-37.ElementName: EMS Personnels Date Length of Service Documented
dPersonnel-37.Definition: The date which the length of EMS service was documented.

dPersonnel-38.Definition: The EMS certification level at which the individual is providing patient care services for the EMS agency.

dPersonnel-39.ElementName: Date of Personnels Certification or Licensure for Agency
dPersonnel-39.Definition: The date that the Certification/Licensure was achieved for the local EMS agency.

dDevice-01.Definition: The unique manufacturers serial number associated with a medical device.

dDevice-02.Definition: The local number or configurable Name/ID of the medical device.

dDevice-04.Definition: The manufacturer of the medical device.

dDevice-05.Definition: The specific manufacturers model number associated with medical device.

dDevice-06.Definition: The date the device was purchased or placed in service by the EMS agency.

dFacility-01.Definition: The type of facility (healthcare or other) that the EMS agency transports patients to or from.

dFacility-03.Definition: The code of the facility as assigned by the state or the EMS agency.

dFacility-04.Definition: The designation(s) associated with the hospital (e.g., Trauma, STEMI, Peds, etc.)

dFacility-05.Definition: The facility National Provider Identifier associated with National Provider System (NPS).

dFacility-06.Definition: The number of the specific room, suite, or apartment of the facility.

dFacility-07.Definition: The address where the facility is located.

dFacility-08.Definition: The city where the facility is located (physical address).

dFacility-09.Definition: The state where the facility is located.

dFacility-10.Definition: The zip code where the facility is located.

dFacility-11.Definition: The county where the facility is located.

dFacility-12.Definition: The country where the facility is located.

dCustomResults-01.Definition: The actual value or values chosen (if values listed in dCustomConfiguration.06) or result (free text, Date/Time, or number) documented for the Custom Data Element
dCustomResults-01.V3Changes: Added to allow customized data elements to be inserted and collected from within the NEMSIS Version 3 standard.

dCustomResults-02.Definition: References the CustomElementID attribute for dCustomConfiguration.CustomGroup

dCustomResults-03.ElementName: CorrelationID of DemographicReport Element or Group
dCustomResults-03.Definition: References the CorrelationID attribute of an element or group in the DemographicReport section
